cat << EOF
Allegro is a multi-platform game library that provides many functions
for graphics, sounds, player input (keyboard, mouse, and joystick), and
timers. It also provides fixed and floating point mathematical functions,
3D functions, file management functions, compressed datafile, and a GUI.
